{
  "texts": [
    "The solid black curves represent the 50% and 90% credible levels of the corresponding GR analysis, i.e.",
    "the analysis with the same starting time but without GR deviations, and the dotted grey curves the same credible levels for the non-GR analysis.",
    "Each subplot refers to one of the events that showed evidence of the mode (3,3).",
    "The samples used are taken from the analysis at the starting time corresponding with the maximum BF in favour of the mode (3, 3), as described in Sect. 6.3 extremely broad bundles in Fig.",
    "5, we believe that a detailed investigation at different starting times is not of interest."
  ]
}